    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "small new rhythms? i don't think i want new rhythms. i just wanted the one we had. it feels like the \"me\" part of me died with him, and i'm just a shell walking around a house that doesn't belong to me anymore. it's not just a \"feeling\" that's heavy... it's the reality that there is no reason to keep going. it's just empty.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your pain is valid, and the feeling of being a hollow shell after loss is incredibly heavy, but thinking about your purpose only when he is present often catches people in the trap of giving up. Many find that healing comes not from finding a new version of themselves immediately, but from slowly remembering they are the foundation of the \"us\" that still lives inside you. Even if it feels impossible right now, reaching out to a grief counselor or a trusted loved one can provide the outside support needed to lighten the load when you feel you have no strength left.",
      "source": "target",
